types.name: Boolean

types.name: CloseWithSwap
types.description: Granular event data for the Loan entity. Emitted when a user closes a loan initiated by a Margin Trade

types.name: Conversion

types.name: ConverterRegistry

fields.description: All the converters (AMM pools) associated with this registry

types.name: DepositCollateral
types.description: Granular event data for the Loan entity. Emitted when a user closes adds collateral to a Margin Trade or Borrow

types.name: ID
types.description: The `ID` scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as `"4"`) or integer (such as `4`) input value will be accepted as an ID.

types.name: Int
types.description: The `Int` scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

fields.name: asset
fields.description: The underlying asset for this pool (eg USDT for the iUSDT pool)

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID is the contract address of the iToken

fields.name: totalAssetLent
fields.description: Total asset volume lent over all time

fields.name: underlyingAsset

types.name: Liquidate

fields.name: id

fields.name: activated

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID is the contract address of the Converter

fields.name: token0
fields.description: The reserve assets of this AMM Pool. The are stored here like this so that they can be accessed inside mappings when the LiquidityPool is loaded.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Sovryn uses Bancor V1 and Bancor V2 pools

types.name: LiquidityPoolAdded

types.name: LiquidityPoolRemoved

types.name: LiquidityPoolToken
types.description:
This entity stores the relationship between liquidity pools and underlying tokens
It also currently stores the total volumes bought and so

fields.name: id

fields.name: poolToken
fields.description: The pool token that represents this token-liquidityPool relationship

types.name: Loan
types.description: A Loan can be initialized by either a Margin Trade event or a Borrow event

fields.name: averageBuyPrice
fields.description: Average price per token from all loan open events

fields.name: averageSellPrice
fields.description: Average price per token from all loan close events

fields.name: borrowedAmount
fields.description: The amount borrowed in loan tokens

fields.name: isOpen
fields.description: If a Liquidate, CloseWithSwap or CloseWithDeposit event occurs with 0 margin or 0 leverage, this property changes to false

fields.name: maximumPositionSize
fields.description: The maximum this position size was - mainly for debugging purposes

fields.name: positionSize
fields.description: Total of collateral (user collateral in a Borrow, and user collateral + borrowed amount in a Trade) in collateral tokens

fields.name: realizedPnL
fields.description: The realized PnL is quoted in the collateral currency

fields.name: startPositionSize
fields.description: Initial size of the position

fields.name: startRate
fields.description: The start rate of the loan in loan tokens (eg if it is a long USD/BTC margin trade, this is the BTC price in USD)

fields.name: totalBought
fields.description: Sum of position volume from Trade, Borrow and DepositCollateral events in this loan, in collateral token

fields.name: totalSold
fields.description: Sum of position change volume from CloseWithSwap, CloseWithDeposit and Liquidate events in this loan, in collateral token

fields.name: type
fields.description: LoanType is either Trade (for Margin Trades) or Borrow (for Borrows)

types.name: PayBorrowingFee
types.description: Granular event data for the Loan entity. Emitted when a user Borrows and when a loan is rolled over

types.name: PayLendingFee
types.description: Granular event data for the Loan entity. Emitted when a user Lends or Unlends and when a loan is rolled over

types.name: PayTradingFee
types.description: Granular event data for the Loan entity. Emitted when a user Margin Trades and when a loan is rolled over

types.name: PoolToken
types.description: For the V1 pools, the pool token and smart token are the same. However, for V2 pools, there is one pool token per asset and only one smart token for the pool.

types.name: ProtocolStats
types.description:
This entity will have only one instance and will be used to store protocol-wide data like list of tokens and number or users.
The ID of this one entity is "0"

fields.name: id
fields.description: Only one entity should be created, with ID "0"

fields.name: tokens
fields.description: An array of all tokens in the protocol

fields.name: totalAmmLpFeesUsd
fields.description: Total volume of fees earned by liquidity providers to AMM pools (in usd)

fields.name: totalAmmStakerFeesUsd
fields.description: Total volume of fees earned by SOV stakers from AMM conversion events (in usd). These fees began after the fee-sharing SIP was executed.

fields.name: totalAmmVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total volume that has passed through every AMM pool of the Sovryn protocol (in usd)

fields.name: totalBorrowVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total of collateral property in Trade event (in usd). This may be changed to borrowed amount volume, but collateral keeps it consistent with margin trading

fields.name: totalBorrowingFeesUsd
fields.description: Total fees from Borrowing earned by SOV stakers (in usd)

fields.name: totalCloseWithDepositVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total volume of Borrows closed (in usd)

fields.name: totalCloseWithSwapVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total position volume closed for Margin Trades (in usd)

fields.name: totalDepositCollateralVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total additional collateral deposited for Margin Trades and Borrows (in usd)

fields.name: totalLendVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total volume supplied to Lending Pools over all time (in usd)

fields.name: totalLendingFeesUsd
fields.description: Total fees from Lending and Unlending earned by SOV stakers (in usd)

fields.name: totalLiquidateVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total Margin Trade and Borrow position size that has been liquidated (in usd)

fields.name: totalMarginTradeVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total of positionSize property in Trade event (in usd). This includes user collateral and borrowed amount

fields.name: totalStakedByVestingSov
fields.description: This is SOV staked by vesting contracts. It in incremented when the contracts stake the tokens, and decremented when users claim their unlocked tokens

fields.name: totalTradingFeesUsd
fields.description: Total fees from Margin Trading earned by SOV stakers (in usd)

fields.name: totalTransactedVolumeUsd
fields.description: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED: This will be a total of volumes of all transaction types (AMM Swaps, Margin Trades, CloseWithSwap etc etc)

fields.name: totalUnlendVolumeUsd
fields.description: Total volume withdrawn from Lending Pool over all time (in usd)

fields.name: totalUsers
fields.description:
Total number of users of the protocol. This number is incremented each time a user initiates a transaction with the Protocol.
Currently this is incremented by specific user actions, but could be incremented on a per Transaction basis.

fields.name: totalVoluntarilyStakedSov
fields.description: This is SOV staked by users (not vesting contracts). It is incremented when users stake tokens, and decremented when users withdraw tokens from the staking contract

types.name: SmartToken
types.description:
The smart token represents a single reserve asset on a single pool.
For V1 pools, there is 1 smart token representing both reserve assets. For V2 pools, there are 2 smart tokens, one for each reserve asset.

fields.name: connectorTokens
fields.description: connectorTokens are the entity that holds the many-to-many relationship between the underlying token asset and the smart token

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID is smart token address

fields.name: liquidityPool
fields.description: The AMM pool this smart token "belongs" to

fields.name: smartTokenType
fields.description: smartTokenType can be Relay or Liquid

types.name: SmartTokenAdded
types.description: Autogenerated for debugging - to be eventually deleted

types.name: SmartTokenRemoved
types.description: Autogenerated for debugging - to be eventually deleted

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

types.name: Swap
types.description:
The Swap entity is an aggregated entity of the individual Conversion events in a transaction.
For example, if a User swaps XUSD to SOV, there will be 2 Conversion events through 2 AMMs (XUSD-BTC and BTC-SOV) in one transaction. These two Conversions are aggregated here.

fields.name: conversions
fields.description: The AMM Conversion events involved in this swap

fields.name: id
fields.description: Transaction hash of this swap

fields.name: isLimit
fields.description: Was this swap a limit order?

fields.name: isMarginTrade
fields.description: Was this swap part of a margin trade?

fields.name: numConversions
fields.description: The number of AMM Conversions involved in this swap (this is primarily for debugging purposes)

fields.name: rate
fields.description: Rate is calculated as toAmount / fromAmount

fields.name: user
fields.description: If this swap was initiated by a contract (for example as part of a Margin Trade), User will be null

fields.name: liquidityPools

fields.name: prevPriceBtc

fields.name: prevPriceUsd
fields.description: previous BTC price used for candleSticks

fields.name: smartTokens
fields.description: The smart tokens that have this token as an underlying asset

fields.name: tokenVolume
fields.description: The total volume of this token that has been traded through the protocol

fields.name: usdVolume
fields.description: The total volume of this token that has been traded through the protocol quoted in USD

fields.name: token

types.name: Transaction

types.name: User
types.description: This entity contains all user-specific data displayed on the dapp, including all user actions

fields.name: borrows
fields.description: An array of Borrow events

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID is user wallet address

fields.name: lendingHistory
fields.description: The lending history of a User, separated into lending pools. Explore the UserLendingHistory entity for more granular events.

fields.name: liquidations
fields.description: An array of Liquidation events linked to this user

fields.name: liquidityHistory
fields.description: An array of all LiquidityAdded and LiquidityRemoved events

fields.name: loans

fields.name: rewardsEarnedHistory
fields.description:
The Rewards history of one user. This includes actions like EarnReward, RewardSovDeposited, and RewardSovStaked.

Swaps here refers to only user-triggered swaps. For example, a swap that is part of a margin trade would not be included.
Swaps involving multiple amm pools are stored as a single swap, comprised of multiple Conversion events

fields.name: votes

fields.name: totalUnlendVolume

fields.name: availableTradingRewards

fields.name: totalFeesAndRewardsEarned
fields.description: This is the total of all EarnReward and RewardClaimed events

types.name: UserTotal
types.description: This is the total volumes of different actions for one user. See ProtocolStats entity for full descriptions.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

enumValues.name: QUERY
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a query operation.

enumValues.name: MUTATION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a mutation operation.

enumValues.name: SUBSCRIPTION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a subscription operation.

enumValues.name: FIELD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment definition.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_SPREAD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment spread.

enumValues.name: INLINE_FRAGMENT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an inline fragment.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a variable definition.

enumValues.name: SCHEMA
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a schema definition.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a scalar definition.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an object type definition.

enumValues.name: FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field definition.

enumValues.name: ARGUMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an argument definition.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an interface definition.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a union definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM_VALUE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum value definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object type definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object field definition.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByURL`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

args.name: reason
args.description: Explains why this element was deprecated, usually also including a suggestion for how to access supported similar data. Formatted using the Markdown syntax, as specified by [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/).

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: specifiedBy
directives.description: Exposes a URL that specifies the behavior of this scalar.

args.name: url
args.description: The URL that specifies the behavior of this scalar.
